Title: Using Projects - CS 302 Fall 1996 - Section 4
Body: We should now be in Borland, and there should be a new window with the title "project" that has something like this in it: [ ] prog6.exe [.exe] ..... | - prog6.cpp [.cpp] This tells us that the project wants to make the program "prog6.exe", and it knows that "prog6.cpp" is used to make that program.
